      "content": "# document models must be added to the vetra drive by default\n\nAfter creating a document model via `createDocument`, it must be added to the vetra drive using `addActions` with an `ADD_FILE` action:\n\n```typescript\naddActions({\n  documentId: \"vetra-{hash}\",  // the vetra drive ID\n  actions: [{\n    type: \"ADD_FILE\",\n    scope: \"global\",\n    input: { id: documentId, ... }\n  }]\n});\n```\n\nSince [[vetra drive holds source documents while preview drive holds instances]], document models (source/definition documents) always go to the vetra drive. Only actual document instances go to the preview drive.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[mcp workflows]]\n- [[architecture decisions]]",
